</div> </div>  </small></h3><p>A repeatable table header.</p>
<p>You should wrap your tables' heading rows in this function even if you do
not plan to wrap your table across pages because Typst uses this function to
attach accessibility metadata to tables and ensure <a href="/docs/guides/accessibility/#basics">Universal
Access</a> to your document.</p>
<p>You can use the <code>repeat</code> parameter to control whether your table's header
will be repeated across pages.</p>
<p>Currently, this function is unsuitable for creating a header column or
single header cells. Either use regular cells, or, if you are exporting a
PDF, you can also use the <a href="/docs/reference/pdf/header-cell/" title="`pdf.header-cell`"><code>pdf.header-cell</code></a> function to mark a cell as a
header cell. Likewise, you can use <a href="/docs/reference/pdf/data-cell/" title="`pdf.data-cell`"><code>pdf.data-cell</code></a> to mark cells in this
